Reasoning: 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper deals with the identification of switched autoregressive linear models, which falls under the domain of systems and control. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses expected values computation and the strong law of large numbers to estimate system dynamics, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a novel methodology for identifying system coefficients and parameters of the noise distribution, which can be considered as an application of artificial intelligence. 
- cs.ST (Statistics): The paper deals with the estimation of system dynamics and parameters of the noise distribution from input-output data, which can be considered as a statistical problem. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper deals with the identification of system coefficients and parameters of the noise distribution from partial information on the probability distribution of the noise, which can be considered as an information-theoretic problem.
